<span id="freeTextContainer14757364155009527793">I&apos;ve said it before, some of these Cadfael stories are wonderful and memorable, others are more easily forgotten. Mostly the later ones, I find. <br/>The Potter&apos;s Field is also a solid, well-told tale, the middle ages are alive and kicking. The case, an unidentifiable female body hastily buried and then uncovered &quot;accidentally&quot; - not really groundbreaking (no pun intended). <br/>Plus of course the endless fight for kingship. Sometimes I wonder what those nobles and kings would say about today&apos;s powers and</span>
